<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED AND 10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON 16709 AND 16710 SERIES - REASSEMBLE - AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT
        ASSEMBLIES AND TIMING
    </stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="assemble" graphiccount="15">
        <title>AUXILIARY COUNTERSHAFT ASSEMBLIES AND TIMING</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">If previously removed, install the countershaft bearings on each of the countershafts (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021f6">Figure 156</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021f6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021f6" filename="../figg13/G13021F6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 156. Countershaft Bearings</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the "O" stamped on each countershaft and mark the adjoining teeth with highly visible
                toolmaker's dye or paint (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021f7">Figure 157</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021f7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021f7" filename="../figg13/G13021F7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 157. Locate "O" Stamp</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the countershafts in a fixture or on a flat bench with the large HI range gears down (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021f8">Figure 158</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021f8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021f8" filename="../figg13/G13021F8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 158. Countershafts In Fixture</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the output shaft, LO range and synchronizer assembly between the two countershafts
                (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021f9">Figure 159</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021f9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021f9" filename="../figg13/G13021F9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 159. LO Range &#38; Synchronizer Assembly</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Check the timing marks on the LO range gear, making sure the countershaft gear timing marks
                are aligned between the LO range gear teeth (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g0">Figure 160</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g0" filename="../figg13/G13021G0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 160. Timing Marks Aligned</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the range yoke assembly into the synchronizer sliding clutch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g1">Figure 161</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g1" filename="../figg13/G13021G1.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 161. Synchronizer Sliding Clutch</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the auxiliary housing over the countershaft assemblies and output shaft assemblies (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g2">Figure 162</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g2" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g2" filename="../figg13/G13021G2.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 162. Auxiliary Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the two rear countershaft bearing races in the auxiliary section bores (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g3">Figure 163</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g3" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g3" filename="../figg13/G13021G3.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 163. Countershaft Bearing Races</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the shim gauges over each bearing. Install bolts: one 3/8 x 2-1/2 inch and two 3/8 x 1
                inch (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g4">left, Figure 164</hotlnk>). TIGHTEN ALL BOLTS ONLY UNTIL SNUG (right). Straps
                may also be used.
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g4" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g4" filename="../figg13/G13021G4.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 164. Shim Gauges Over Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the range cylinder into the auxiliary section bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g5">left, Figure 165</hotlnk>). Tighten bolts to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226;
                m) (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g5" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g5" filename="../figg13/G13021G5.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 165. Install Range Cylinder</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Place the range piston in the cylinder bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g6">left, Figure 166</hotlnk>). Tighten the piston retaining nut to 70 to 85
                ft-lbs. (95 to 115 N&#8226; m) (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g6" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g6" filename="../figg13/G13021G6.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 166. Range Piston In Cylinder Bore</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position new gasket and range cylinder cover on the range cylinder and tighten to
                recommended torque (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g7">Figure 167</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g7" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g7" filename="../figg13/G13021G7.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 167. Gasket &#38; Range Cylinder Cover</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the bearing spacer on the output shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g8">left, Figure 168</hotlnk>). Heat the rear bearing cone and install the bearing
                on the output shaft until seated (right).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g8" filename="../figg13/G13021G8.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 168. Bearing Spacer</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Do not heat the bearing above 275&#176;F (136&#176;C). Use a bearing heater if possible.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Locate the rear bearing cover and gasket on the housing. Apply Loctite 242 to the bolt
                threads and tighten bolts to 35 to 45 ft-lbs. (47 to 61 N&#8226; m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021g9">left, Figure 169</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021g9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021g9" filename="../figg13/G13021G9.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 169. Apply Loctite 242</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>One rear bearing bolt hole is chamfered. The nylon collar and brass washer must be installed
                        at this location to correctly seal the rear bearing cover. DO NOT REUSE OLD NYLON COLLAR.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Spacer must be installed between bearing and speedometer drive gear (right).</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the output yoke and nut on the output shaft for installation of auxiliary section to
                the main case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13021h0">Figure 170</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13021h0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13021h0" filename="../figg13/G13021H0.webp" type="webp" scalefit="0"/>
                <caption>Figure 170. Install Output Yoke</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
